<br>
To this day, I'm sure I could make many a mathematical error that would cause a few rolled eyes, but language is something I'm good at, and it annoys me to see it misused.  Honestly, it's nothing that I have against the speaker/writer, but it's something like... If you were to have a song you loved more than any other, and you saw it played in a commercial for something you loathe.  It's aggravating, but you realize after some thought that not every person may see what you see in that song, or understand it as you do, or even, in some cases, see that it has value.  So, you move on, as I do when I see people in a thread about grammar typing the word grammer.  It's a pet peeve. Nothing more. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Kelisk Mae'Lokh</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Chancellor of Skathris Ven'Sho--Patriarch of Cabilis</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=112815"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Inspect Kelisk?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=blinkun12>Blinkun12</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 79<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/15/03 1:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3868.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Spelling and age. (or should be it speling?)</span><hr size=1> Well I DID win school wide spelling bees.  Do I care at all?  No I do not.<br>
<br>
I was watching TV a few years ago and this character who was an immigrant from the former soviet union was being offered a plea bargain.  The terms were less than stellar from his perspective.  His reply which I think is the most relevant quote in this discussion is.<br>
<br>
&quot;Just because I speak with an accent doesn't mean I am stupid.  In Russia I was a rocket scientist.&quot;<br>
<br>
The point is that some people can't spell well.  They just can't.  I can spell very well.  My girlfriend who is an english major and much more able to write persuasively can not spell well.  My spelling has nothing to do with my ability to write.<br>
<br>
Now sometimes there is the case where spelling mistakes are not a issue of inability but of indifference.  When you see the word &quot;teh&quot; instead of &quot;the&quot;, it gives the impression that the typist put less thought into their post as they didn't take the half second to hit delete twice and correct the mistake that they must be aware of. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.eqfaces.com/photos2/blinkun_copy1.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
