<br>
I also have to rely on spell checkers to catch mistyped words.<br>
<br>
But I am also British and I get annoyed by being told that Colour shouldn't have the 'u' or that I've used an 's' and not a 'z', or that the spell checker (set to British English !?!) doesn't know what Gaol is! (Pop to PoJ and take a look at the Gaolers... goes to show that Sony know the correct spelling for some things <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
<br>
But all that is in using text editors. In EQ, there's no spell checker, and it is easy to suffer 'dyslexia' of the fingers (type quickly and hit keys in the wrong order). It's not so bad here - you can spot such errors easier, but on a single line strip?<br>
<br>
No, forgive people's mistyping, even their mistakes in Grammar. Look at what they are trying to say and judge that.<br>
<br>
But 'l33t' writing... *shudder* No... that turns my stomach! Not needed, not wanted and it does not show the person to be anything but someone trying to impress - which is doesn't.<br>
<br>
... and neither does vulgarity. It's not needed in a well written text <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :hat --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/pimp.gif ALT=":hat"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
