<br>
This is a good subject.  I have to admit that I have been a lazy typer from time to time in chat.  I'm trying not to do it anymore.  When pressed for time, I would say things like, &quot;how r u?&quot;  Once I realized that this might be construed as D00d speak, I decided to quit being so lazy.  By the way, I'm STILL trying to figure out what L33t means.  Someone enlighten me, because I don't get it.<br>
<br>
Other subjects.  I agree with Duplicitas, I speak English not American or U.K. English.  We have different 'terms' for things, but it is the same language.<br>
<br>
Additionally, I think it's wonderful that some of you can speak English as a second language.  Though, it is my first language, I do know that it is a difficult one to learn.  I applaud anyone who learns it and becomes fluent in it.<br>
<br>
I do think that some of us are guilty of being lazy in typing and in spelling.  I know that while in chat it's easier to make mistakes, and I'm usually correcting my spelling before I hit enter.  But it does slow me down.  When I'm writing a message, like this one, I take my time and consider structure and the message that I would like to deliver.<br>
<br>
Maybe that's the answer.  Maybe we should all slow down a little. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~smclynch/images/DriaSig3.png" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=driaann>DriaAnn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/17/03 1:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3868.topic&index=31>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~smclynch/images/dria.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_tongue.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Spelling and Grammar</span><hr size=1> ACK!  Then I go and so something stupid like say 'Typer' instead of 'Typist'.<br>
